This paper focuses on the technical analysis of adware, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the evolution of the adware over time, which could be considered a software engineering (cs.SE) aspect. The analysis of the adware's data collection and encryption methods could also fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the potential security risks posed by adware, which could be considered a distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) aspect. Finally, the paper discusses the technical details of the adware's implementation, which could be considered a programming languages (cs.PL) aspect.
